<title>USA: Delta says changes noncontract pay, benefits.</title>
<headline>Delta says changes noncontract pay, benefits.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-04-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Delta Air Lines Inc said it Thursday it informed its non-contract domestic employees of &quot;changes&quot; in compensation and benefits.</p>
<p>Delta said these actions &quot;keep salaries in line with industry standards and represent an increased investment in Delta people of approximately $137 million a year.&quot;</p>
<p>Pay increases are effective July 1, 1997, Delta said.  </p>
<p>Delta said it was making the changes to &quot;keep its people at or near the top in salary and benefits in the airline industry.&quot;  It did not give details.</p>
